burlap.oomdp.singleagent

Class GroundedAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • burlap.oomdp.singleagent.GroundedAction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AbstractGroundedAction
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BeliefMDPGenerator.GroundedBeliefAction, ObjectParameterizedAction.ObjectParameterizedGroundedAction, Policy.GroundedAnnotatedAction, SGToSADomain.GroundedSAAActionWrapper

    public class GroundedAction
extends java.lang.Object
implements AbstractGroundedAction
    A GroundedAction is a high-level implementation of a AbstractGroundedAction that is closely associated with single-agent Action definitions. The role of a GroundedAction is to provide a reference to its corresponding Action definition and also provide parameter assignments with which its Action should be applied. The set of possible GroundedAction instances specifying the different possible parameter assignments will be generated by the associated Action.getAllApplicableGroundedActions(burlap.oomdp.core.states.State) method. See the Action class documentation for more information on implementing parameterized Action definitions.

    This high-level class can be used directly, without subclassing, for any parameter-less Action definitions and should be subclassed for any parameterized Action definitions (with the subclass instances returned by the associated Action.getAllApplicableGroundedActions(burlap.oomdp.core.states.State) and Action.getAssociatedGroundedAction() method). The GroundedAction subclass can store the parameter assignment data any way you like.

    If you plan on making an Action definition with OO-MDP object parameters, you can use the existing ObjectParameterizedAction, which is associated with the GroundedAction subclass ObjectParameterizedAction.ObjectParameterizedGroundedAction.

    When you subclass GroundedAction to provide parameter information, you should override the following methods:
    copy()
    initParamsWithStringRep(String[])
    getParametersAsString()
    The copy() method should be override to return a new instance of your subclass with all parameter assignment information copied over. The initParamsWithStringRep(String[]) should be overridden to allow a String array specification of parameters to be provided to initialize them. Overriding this method is not critical, but is useful for serialization purposes. The getParametersAsString() similarly should returns a String array representing the String value of each parameter. As with the initParamsWithStringRep(String[]) method, overriding getParametersAsString() is not critical, but is useful for serialization and similar processes.

    In addition to specifying parameter assignment information for a Action definition, this class also provides a number of useful shortcut methods for evaluating the GroundedAction. Specifically, see the
    executeIn(burlap.oomdp.core.states.State)
    executeIn(burlap.oomdp.singleagent.environment.Environment)
    getTransitions(burlap.oomdp.core.states.State) and
    applicableInState(burlap.oomdp.core.states.State)
    methods, which call the associated Action methods providing this instance as the set of parameters to use. Note that the getTransitions(burlap.oomdp.core.states.State) method will throw a runtime exception if the associated Action definition does not implement the FullActionModel interface.
    Author:
    James MacGlashan

      • translateParameters

        public GroundedAction translateParameters(State source,
                                 State target)
        A helper method that handles action translate in case this GroundedAction implements AbstractObjectParameterizedGroundedAction. Works by calling the AbstractObjectParameterizedGroundedAction.Helper.translateParameters(burlap.oomdp.core.AbstractGroundedAction, burlap.oomdp.core.states.State, burlap.oomdp.core.states.State) method with this object as the action to translate. If this is a AbstractObjectParameterizedGroundedAction, then a new GroundedAction with its object parameters mapped to the object names sin the target state is returned.
        Parameters:
        source - the source state in which this GroundedAction's parameters were bound.
        target - the target state in which the returned GroundedAction will have its parameters bound.
        Returns:
        If this is a AbstractObjectParameterizedGroundedAction, then a new GroundedAction with its object parameters mapped to the object names sin the target state
